{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TUIkit’s preference system enables ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"bottom-up data flow"}]},{"text":": the reverse of environment values. While the environment passes data down from parent to child, preferences let child views publish values that ancestors can observe and react to.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The system mirrors SwiftUI’s preference API and consists of three parts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceKey"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Protocol that defines a named value type with a default and a reduce strategy"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceValues"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Type-safe storage that holds all preference values for a scope"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceStorage"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Stack-based collector that manages preference contexts per render pass"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A built-in example is "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey"},{"type":"text","text":": a child view sets "},{"code":".navigationTitle(\"Settings\")","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and the enclosing navigation container reads that preference to render the title bar."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Defining-a-Preference-Key","text":"Defining a Preference Key","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A preference key declares what type of value it carries and how multiple values from sibling children are combined:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct CounterKey: PreferenceKey {","    static let defaultValue: Int = 0","","    static func reduce(value: inout Int, nextValue: () -> Int) {","        value += nextValue()","    }","}"]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"defaultValue","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Returned when no child has set this preference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce(value:nextValue:)"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Combines values when multiple children set the same key"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The default ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"text":" implementation simply takes the last value. Override it when you need additive behavior (summing counts), array collection, or other merge strategies.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Setting-a-Preference","text":"Setting a Preference","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Child views publish a preference using the "},{"code":".preference(key:value:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct ItemView: View {","    var body: some View {","        Text(\"Item\")","            .preference(key: CounterKey.self, value: 1)","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Under the hood, this wraps the view in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceModifier"},{"type":"text","text":" that calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"preferences.setValue(_:forKey:)"},{"type":"text","text":" during rendering. The value is reduced into the current scope using the key’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"type":"text","text":" function."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Observing-Preferences","text":"Observing Preferences","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ancestor views react to collected preferences using ","type":"text"},{"code":".onPreferenceChange(_:perform:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct ItemList: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            ItemView()","            ItemView()","            ItemView()","        }","        .onPreferenceChange(CounterKey.self) { totalCount in","            \/\/ totalCount == 3 (three children each set value: 1, additive reduce)","        }","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The modifier pushes a new preference context, renders all children (which set their preferences), pops the context, and fires the callback with the accumulated result."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"The-Navigation-Title-Shortcut","text":"The Navigation Title Shortcut","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit provides "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a built-in preference key with a convenience modifier:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct SettingsPage: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Text(\"App settings go here\")","        }","        .navigationTitle(\"Settings\")","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NavigationTitleKey"},{"type":"text","text":" uses the default "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"type":"text","text":" (last value wins), so the deepest child’s title takes precedence."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"How-Preferences-Flow-per-Frame","text":"How Preferences Flow per Frame","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Preferences are collected fresh every frame. Here’s the lifecycle within a single render pass:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reset"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RenderLoop.render()"},{"text":" calls ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"preferences.beginRenderPass()"},{"text":", clearing all callbacks and resetting the stack to a single empty context","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set"}]},{"type":"text","text":": As the view tree renders top-down, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceModifier"},{"type":"text","text":" views call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"setValue(_:forKey:)"},{"type":"text","text":", which reduces values into the current stack frame"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scope"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"code":"OnPreferenceChangeModifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" pushes a new context before rendering its subtree, isolating child preferences","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Collect"}]},{"text":": After the subtree finishes, the modifier pops the context (merging into the parent) and fires the callback with the scoped result","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Discard","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": At the start of the next frame, everything resets: stale preferences never persist","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This per-frame reset ensures preferences always reflect the current view tree. Removed views stop contributing automatically."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Reduce-Strategies","text":"Reduce Strategies","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"type":"text","text":" function determines how multiple children’s values combine. Common patterns:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strategy"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use Case","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Last value wins"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value = nextValue()"},{"type":"text","text":" (default)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Titles, labels: deepest child wins"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Additive","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value += nextValue()"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Counting items, summing heights","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Array collection"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value.append(contentsOf: nextValue())"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Gathering menu items, breadcrumbs","type":"text"}]}]]],"type":"table"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Array collection example","struct BreadcrumbKey: PreferenceKey {","    static let defaultValue: [String] = []","","    static func reduce(value: inout [String], nextValue: () -> [String]) {","        value.append(contentsOf: nextValue())","    }","}"]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"TUIkit"}],"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Preferences"},"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/tuikit\/preferences"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Pass data from child views up to their ancestors."}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Preferences"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StateManagement","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ThemingGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusSystem","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StatusBarGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppearanceAndColors","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/CustomViews","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/KeyboardShortcuts","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PaletteReference","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ListAndTable","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/LayoutSystem"],"generated":true,"title":"Guides","anchor":"Guides"}],"references":{"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/NavigationTitleKey":{"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"NavigationTitleKey"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A preference key for the navigation title.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NavigationTitleKey"}],"title":"NavigationTitleKey","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/navigationtitlekey"},"tuikit-logo.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/TUIkit\/tuikit-logo.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"tuikit-logo.png","alt":"TUIkit Logo"},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/ThemingGuide":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ThemingGuide","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/themingguide","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Customize the visual appearance of your TUIkit application with palettes."}],"title":"Theming Guide"},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/StateManagement":{"title":"State Management","type":"topic","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StateManagement","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/statemanagement","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage reactive state in your TUIkit application."}]},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/FocusSystem":{"title":"Focus System","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/focussystem","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Navigate between interactive elements using the keyboard.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusSystem","role":"article"},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/AppearanceAndColors":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Control border styles, visual appearances, and the color system.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/appearanceandcolors","role":"article","type":"topic","title":"Appearance and Colors","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppearanceAndColors"},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/PaletteReference":{"url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/palettereference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PaletteReference","title":"Palette Reference","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A visual reference for all built-in color palettes with their exact color values."}]},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/KeyboardShortcuts":{"title":"Keyboard Shortcuts","abstract":[{"text":"How keyboard input flows through TUIkit: from raw terminal bytes to your view handlers.","type":"text"}],"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/keyboardshortcuts","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/KeyboardShortcuts","kind":"article"},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit":{"type":"topic","title":"TUIkit","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A declarative, SwiftUI-like framework for building Terminal User Interfaces in Swift."}],"kind":"symbol","images":[{"identifier":"tuikit-logo.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"tuikit-logo.png","type":"card"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit","role":"collection"},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/StatusBarGuide":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StatusBarGuide","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/statusbarguide","title":"Status Bar","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Configure the shortcut bar at the bottom of the terminal."}]},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/CustomViews":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/customviews","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/CustomViews","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build your own views by composing existing ones or creating custom view modifiers."}],"title":"Custom Views","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/ListAndTable":{"title":"List and Table Components","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ListAndTable","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/listandtable","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build scrollable, navigable data collections with keyboard support."}],"type":"topic","role":"article"},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/LayoutSystem":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand the two-pass layout used by stacks and other layout containers."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/LayoutSystem","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/layoutsystem","title":"Layout System","role":"article"}}}